<SECTION>
<P>
Ventura County Life; Part J; Page 24 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
368 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
SHOP TALK; NIGHTS IN BLACK SATIN DRAW NEAR; CALIFORNIA'S CASUAL CHIC TAKES A 
HOLIDAY FOR SEASONAL GLAMOUR. AND DRESS-UP APPAREL CAN BE FOUND FOR A LOW-DOWN 
PRICE. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE SAWYER, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Here in sunny Southern California, "The Look" has always been casual. 
Peoplewear jeans almost everywhere, even to the theater, fine restaurants and 
parties. If you are one of those women who love to dress up, you're either 
terribly frustrated or you're making plans to move to New York. 
</P>
<P>
 But the holiday season does offer a brief window of opportunity for you. These 
few weeks of holiday parties -- and especially New Year's Eve -- are about the 
only time you can dress in your finery and not draw snickers. 
</P>
<P>
 The fashion magazines have been screaming "Glamour Is Back!" throughout this 
past season. Happily, the stores are full of velvet, silk and mohair. If you 
look in the right places, you just might find some glamorous clothes at prices 
low enough to leave room in your budget for more jeans and T-shirts in the new 
year. 
</P>
<P>
 Heeding the call for more glamour, and copying big-name designers, the Gap has 
truly outdone itself. One personal favorite is a long-sleeved, ankle-length 
black velvet dress for $68. We also picked out a long black slip-dress in silk 
for $39.99. This looks great with one of the mohair cardigans (if only we could 
bear the scratching) for $42. 
</P>
<P>
 The Gap also has a great selection of luxe accessories, including velvet hats 
($16.50) and silk and velvet scarves ($26). Velvet evening bags and crocheted 
backpacks are offered at $24 and $38. 
</P>
<P>
 At Ross Dress for Less, there were velvet tunic tops by BCBG Paris for just 
$29.99, down from the original price of $84. Another favorite was a crocheted 
mohair pullover in silvery gray by the Limited for $19.99 (from $50). 
</P>
<P>
 At Marshall's, we admired velvet coordinates by ABS from $39.99 to $79.99. 
Silk blouses by KIKIT were $29.99, down from $96. 
</P>
<P>
 Say you've got a really special occasion coming up . . . like New Year's Eve 
with Warren and Annette. Try Designer Labels for Less in the Oxnard Factory 
Outlet. The men's store carries drop-dead gorgeous formal wear for men and 
women. (We've even seen black label Giorgio Armani in the past.) 
</P>
<P>
 Currently, they've got Donna Karan and Ralph Lauren dresses and gowns at 60% 
to 80% off retail. 
</P>
<P>
 Whatever you decide, don't forget the red lipstick and the high heels. 
Fabulous, darling! 
</P>
