<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL JOURNAL: COMPTON; CITY EXTENDS DEADLINE ON CARD CLUB PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PSYCHE PASCUAL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 City officials have given a developer another six months to secure a deal with 
a financial partner to build a card club in the city. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council voted 4 to 1 last week to set a new deadline of June 13, 
1995, to begin construction.Councilwoman Yvonne Arceneaux opposed the 
extension.  
</P>
<P>
 It is the second extension granted to the developer, Compton Entertainment 
Inc., which requested the delay to finalize an agreement with the investor, 
Hollywood Park Inc. In July, Hollywood Park opened a casino at the Inglewood 
track. 
</P>
<P>
 Hollywood Park spokesman Tyrone Smith assured council members last week that 
the company is interested in investing in the $40-million casino project, which 
would be built on a seven-acre site off Auto Drive South, near the Artesia (91) 
Freeway. PSYCHE PASCUAL 
</P>
</TEXT>
