<HEADLINE>
<P>
CITY HALL JOURNAL: SIGNAL HILL; SEPARATE ZIP CODE, POST OFFICE SOUGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE EAMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city has asked the U.S. Postal Service to give Signal Hill its own ZIP 
code and post office. 
</P>
<P>
 By unanimous vote, the City Council directed City Manager Douglas N. La Belle 
to write a letter asking Long Beach Postmaster Ed Jenkins to include a new post 
office in the Postal Service's five-year capital improvement plan. 
</P>
<P>
 If Jenkins includes a Signal Hill facility in the five-year plan, the Postal 
Service will ask all Signal Hill residents and businesses whether they want 
their own ZIP code. The Postal Service will build the post office if a majority 
supports the new ZIP code. 
</P>
<P>
 Signal Hill, which is surrounded by Long Beach, is served by three Long Beach 
post offices, each with a separate ZIP code. STEVE EAMES 
</P>
</TEXT>
