<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: LONG BEACH; JOB CENTER PLANNED FOR FORMER NAVAL SITE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JILL GOTTESMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 An $18.6-million job-training center is planned for a former naval housing 
site in west Long Beach, federal officials announced this month. 
</P>
<P>
 The center will be built on 17 acres at the former Savannah-Cabrillo housing 
project, and will be operated by the U.S. Department of Labor. It will house up 
to 264 students in dorms on the site. 
</P>
<P>
 When completed at the end of 1996, the center will offer job training mainly 
to low-income Long Beach residents between 16 and 24 years old. Trades such as 
auto repair, landscaping, telecommunications and tile installation will be 
taught at the center. JILL GOTTESMAN 
</P>
