</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; RAMS; WRIGHT REPLACES NEWMAN AS STARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By T.J. SIMERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Safety Anthony Newman, who has started the last 46 games, will take a seat on 
the bench Sunday so the Rams can take a look at rookie Toby Wright. 
</P>
<P>
 "I've been struggling the past three or four games," Newman said. "If I'm 
going to hurt the team I shouldn't be out there. I've been pressing, and I 
haven't been taking care of business. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a good wake-up call, and to be honest, it takes some pressure off my 
back. I've been thinking and thinking about why we're not winning, and then 
there's been all the talk about the move and this is almost like a break. It's 
a demotion, but I can rest my mind." 
</P>
<P>
 On Monday, Coach Chuck Knox said the team would play its best players in an 
attempt to win the last two games, rather than experiment and play young 
players such as Wright, quarterback Tommy Maddox and defensive end Brad Ottis. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rams will use Wright at strong safety and move Marquez Pope to free safety 
on early downs. They will bring in rookie safety Keith Lyle on passing downs. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Tackle Jackie Slater, who is wrapping up season No. 19, said he is close to 
making a decision on his future. Slater, who has been sidelined because of an 
elbow injury, indicated before the season that he would like to play 20 years. 
"He hasn't said this is his last year," Knox said. "I think he probably could 
play another year; he'd played well when he was healthy." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Rams added linebacker Brett Collins, who was with the team earlier this 
season, to their 53-man roster because of injuries to linebackers Tom Homco 
(foot) and Chris Martin (calf). The Rams put rookie tackle Ronald Edwards on 
injured reserve because of bone spurs in his ankle. Knox said Edwards suffered 
the injury in training camp. T.J. SIMERS 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA121594-0087 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 108191 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
December 15, 1994, Thursday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
