<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: AUTOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Dealer Satisfaction With Auto Makers Flat: Car and truck dealers may be 
selling everything in sight and collecting bigger profits this year, but their 
satisfaction with auto makers hasn't grown, a new survey says. J.D. Power & 
Associates said its annual index of dealer attitudes shows no improvement in 
how dealers feel about car companies.The main reason is too much success, the 
Agoura Hills marketing firm said. Auto makers can't build enough hot-selling 
models to meet buyer demand. Auto makers have streamlined their operations to 
respond more quickly when demand increases. But the new, leaner operations 
can't build popular models fast enough in a year when overall vehicle sales are 
up more than 8%. 
</P>
