<P>
ATTORNEYS MEET AS NHL GOES NOWHERE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By HELENE ELLIOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With only about a week left to save the season, attorneys for the NHL and its 
players' union met informally Wednesday in New York. 
</P>
<P>
 The session was designed to clear up issues that bogged down previous sessions 
and to set guidelines for future talks involving full delegations. A meeting is 
scheduled for today. 
</P>
<P>
 Commissioner Gary Bettman and union chief Bob Goodenow spoke by telephone but 
aren't expected to meet before Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 A league source cautioned against reading anything into the lack of full-scale 
talks. However, a management source said Wednesday's meeting didn't accomplish 
enough to warrant summoning all the negotiators today. HELENE ELLIOTT 
