<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SENIORS; ACHIEVEMENTS, ACTIVITIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By COMPILED BY ALAN EYERLY WITH BERT ELJERA, LYNN FRANEY, RUSS LOAR AND HOLLY 
J. WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 WESTMINSTER: Applicants Accepted for New Apartments 
</P>
<P>
 Application forms are now available for people 60 and older who are interested 
in renting an apartment at the Rose Gardens senior complex near Westminster's 
Civic Center. Construction of the 132-unit complex is scheduled for completion 
by late this month and tenants are expected to start moving in by January. 
</P>
<P>
 To qualify, a person living alone must have an annual income of $24,720 or 
less. For two people, the income limit is $28,200 a year. 
</P>
<P>
 People who qualify will be selected by lottery. 
</P>
<P>
 For information, call Solari Enterprises, Inc. at (714) 284-8448. CYPRESS: 
Senior Center Now Offers Books on Tape 
</P>
<P>
 Books on tape are now available at the Cypress Senior Citizens Center. 
Selections include bestsellers, romance novels, Westerns and classics. 
</P>
<P>
 Tapes and players must remain at the center, 9031 Grindlay St. south of 
Lincoln Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 The center is open from 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. Monday through Friday, and only on 
special events in the evenings and weekends. Information: (714) 229-6776. 
TUSTIN: Support Groups Meet All Through Week 
</P>
<P>
 A variety of support groups are being offered at the Tustin Area Senior 
Center. 
</P>
<P>
 A bereavement group meets from 1 to 2:30 p.m. on the first and third Mondays, 
an Alzheimer's group meets from 3:30 to 5 p.m. on the second Tuesday, and a 
Parkinson's group meets from 1 to 2:30 p.m. on the fourth Monday of the month. 
</P>
<P>
 The center is at 200 S. C St. Information: (714) 573-3340. NEWPORT BEACH: Help 
for Adults With Aging Parents 
</P>
<P>
 Oasis Senior Center in Newport Beach is starting a support group for adults 
with aging parents. Topics are geared to people who are caring for their 
parents and want to exchange ideas about how to cope with the changes brought 
on by aging and the stress they put on the family. 
</P>
<P>
 The group will meet from 6:30 to 8 p.m. the second Wednesday of each month at 
the center, 800 Marguerite Ave., Corona del Mar. Information: (714) 644-3244. 
IRVINE: New Musical Group Seeks Singers, Players 
</P>
<P>
 A new singing group is forming at the Lakeside Senior Center. 
</P>
<P>
 The group is seeking singers, piano players and other instrumentalists. 
Rehearsals are held from 11 a.m. to 1 p.m. Tuesdays and Fridays at the Lakeview 
Senior Center, 20 Lake Road. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (714) 997-0403. 
</P>
</TEXT>
