<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; ORANGE; GIFTS ARE NEEDED FOR INMATES' 
CHILDREN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LESLEY WRIGHT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 At least 350 children whose parents are in prison will celebrate Christmas a 
little early this year. 
</P>
<P>
 Friends Outside will have its 10th annual holiday party for the children from 
1:30 to 4:30 p.m. Saturday at the Orange Senior Center.But organizers lack 
about 100 gift-filled stockings, said program director Sandi Burns. 
</P>
<P>
 All of the children are from Orange County but their parents are in prisons 
across the state. 
</P>
<P>
 "Many times, especially through the holidays, the separation is very sad," 
Burns said. "The kids love the party. They look forward to it every year. . . . 
For most of them, their lives are filled with a lot of despair."  
</P>
<P>
 The group likes to give each child a stocking filled with small gifts such as 
crayons, candy or books, Burns said. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone wishing to donate a stocking should call the group at (714) 836-8100. 
LESLEY WRIGHT 
</P>
</TEXT>
