<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: SADDLEBACK / SOUTH BEACH; SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO; 
APPLICATIONS SOUGHT FOR CITY PANEL SEATS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city is accepting applications for two vacant seats on the Planning 
Commission. 
</P>
<P>
 The openings were created by the resignation of Cheryle Hodge and the election 
of Wyatt T. Hart to the City Council. 
</P>
<P>
 Also, the city has a vacancy on its Mobile Home Park Review Committee, caused 
by the election of David M. Swerdlin to the council. 
</P>
<P>
 The openings are expected to be filled during the City Council's Jan. 3 
meeting. 
</P>
<P>
 City residents who want to apply may pick up forms from 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. 
weekdays at City Hall, 32400 Paseo Adelanto. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 493-1171.JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
