<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; HUGE FIRST HALF KEY TO VICTORY FOR OCEAN VIEW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Faced with the possibility of meeting highly touted Mater Dei in the 
semifinals, an inspired Ocean View scored 51 points in the first half of a 
78-44 drubbing of Newport Harbor in a quarterfinal game in the Tournament of 
Champions Wednesday at Ocean View High. 
</P>
<P>
 "Everything went our way," Ocean View Coach Jim Harris said."A game like this 
was out of (Newport Harbor Coach) Richard Smith's hands." 
</P>
<P>
 The Seahawks (6-3) forced 31 turnovers with their pressure defense, then 
carved up the Sailors by making 28 layups. Ocean View shot 72% from the field 
in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 Dan McDonald, a 6-foot-1 senior forward, scored most of his 23 points inside. 
Mike Seguin added 18 points and Alejandro Enriquez 14. 
</P>
<P>
 But Ocean View will get the toughest of tests in Friday's semifinal against 
Mater Dei, a 58-50 winner over Los Angeles Fairfax.  
</P>
<P>
 "We talked about the winner getting to play Mater Dei in the next round and 
the kids responded," Harris said. "Man-for-man, Mater Dei is awesome. I don't 
know if anyone matches up with them on paper. 
</P>
<P>
 "But if we go out and play good team basketball, anything can happen on the 
court. Hey, if we had a chance to play Dream Team 2, we'd do it." 
</P>
<P>
 Will Rankin scored 17 points for Newport Harbor (4-4). MICHAEL ITAGAKI 
</P>
</TEXT>
