<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' SOCCER ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In other nonleague soccer: 
</P>
<P>
 Anaheim 1, La Habra 1 -- Elmer Rivas scored on a penalty kick in the second 
half to tie the score for Anaheim. La Habra (3-0-2) got a first-half goal from 
Grant Froman. Jesus Acevedo had eight saves and Travis Pena had five for 
Anaheim (0-3-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Buena Park 3, Rancho Alamitos 2 -- George Calderon scored midway through the 
second half to break a 2-2 tie and goalie Aaron Hudson had 11 saves to preserve 
the victory for the Coyotes (4-3-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley 2, Huntington Beach 0 -- Todd Weidner scored both goals for 
host Capistrano Valley (7-2-1). 
</P>
<P>
 Century 2, Costa Mesa 1 -- Hugo Alvardo scored the winning goal for Century 
(4-2-1) early in the second half. Juan Ponce, with an assist from Rigo Munguia, 
scored the Centurion's first goal a minute before Alvardo's. Costa Mesa's goal 
came on a penalty kick. 
</P>
<P>
 Esperanza 2, Canyon 2 -- Clay Kilbarger scored on a header from Todd Stearman 
with about a minute left to earn a tie for host Canyon (3-3-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Foothill 1, San Clemente 1 -- Craig Akin scored for San Clemente (1-2-1) and 
Stephan Johnson scored for host Foothill (3-1-2). 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills 2, Westminster 2 -- Manuel Tapia scored with a minute left to 
give Westminster a 2-1 lead, but Mike Thorpe scored with 30 seconds left for 
Laguna Hills (4-2-2). Joey Gummere also scored for Westminster (2-2-2) and 
Kevin McConaughy scored for Laguna Hills. 
