<HEADLINE>
<P>
NORTH HOLLYWOOD TOURNAMENT; MILLER PUTS ON FINISHING TOUCH, 69-68 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL LAZARUS, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chatsworth High center Eddie Miller wasn't able to start Wednesday night 
against Grant, but he was able to finish off the Lancers. 
</P>
<P>
 Miller made a six-foot bank shot after an offensive rebound with 19 seconds 
remaining to give the Chancellors a 69-68 victory in the first round of the 
North Hollywood tournament. The Chancellors will play Banning, a 77-55 winner 
over El Camino Real, in the second round tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 Miller was not in the starting lineup because he missed two days of practice 
because of a minor thigh injury. But he dominated once he entered midway though 
the first quarter, finishing with 19 points and 21 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 "I felt good while I was stretching beforehand and I knew I was ready to go," 
Miller said. 
</P>
<P>
 Grant had a chance to win the game on an inbounds play with four seconds left, 
but Donald Patterson missed an 18-foot shot from the baseline. 
</P>
<P>
 Ronald Patterson, Donald's brother, scored 30 points for Grant. He hit three 
times from three-point range in the fourth quarter to lead the Lancers back 
from a 13-point deficit entering the quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Ronald Patterson's three-pointer with slightly more than two minutes remaining 
made the score 65-65. 
</P>
<P>
 Chatsworth's Tariq Hill made two free throws and Ronald Patterson one free 
throw before a driving layup by Freddy Ramirez with 43 seconds left gave Grant 
(4-3) a 68-67 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 "We lost our concentration and guys were getting into foul trouble," Miller 
said. "We lost one to Carson that was just like this and we didn't want that 
again." 
</P>
<P>
 Chatsworth (3-1) had 19 turnovers, 18 in the last three quarters. 
</P>
<P>
 "So far this season, we've been a peak-and-valley team," Chatsworth Coach Bill 
Whiting said. "That part was one of the valleys." 
</P>
<P>
 Hill finished with 24 points and made three of five three-point shots. Guard 
Jerome Joseph added 11 points and seven rebounds for the Chancellors. 
</P>
<P>
 Taj Rollins scored 14 points for Grant, 12 in the second half. Donald 
Patterson finished with eight points. 
</P>
<P>
 In other first-round games: 
</P>
<P>
 Banning 77, El Camino Real 55 -- The Pilots (7-1) used full court pressure and 
21 points from Harold McCrimmon to dominate the Conquistadores (1-6), who got 
25 points from Jermel Jones. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Monroe 84, Garfield 64 -- The Vikings (4-3) used an 18-3 run in the second 
half to break open an game that was tied, 45-45. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 North Hollywood 77, Granada Hills 67 -- Mike Delano scored nine of his 24 
points in the fourth quarter to lead the Huskies (4-2), who got 24 more from 
Shannon Johnson. 
</P>
<P>
 Ernest Quinley had 28 points for Granada Hills (3-4) and William Ruffin added 
19. 
</P>
</TEXT>
