<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: REDONDO BEACH; 7 TO VIE FOR COUNCIL, CITY TREASURER POSTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES BENNING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Seven candidates have filed papers for two City Council seats and three for 
the city treasurer's post in the March 7 municipal elections. City Clerk John 
L. Oliver, whose term also expires, is unopposed. 
</P>
<P>
 City Treasurer Alice E. DeLong, under attack for allegedly mistreating 
employees, will face two opponents in her bid for reelection. Ernie O'Dell, 51, 
the city's Chamber of Commerce director, and Armondo Herrera, 51, a supervisor 
in DeLong's office, plan to run for the $78,600-a-year post. 
</P>
<P>
 In District 3, the south-central portion of the city, Councilman Stevan Colin 
is barred from seeking reelection because of term limits. Four candidates will 
compete for his seat. 
</P>
<P>
 William N. Gaillard, a 42-year-old salesman, and Steve Bopp, a 46-year-old 
sales representative, both filed papers, as did Mike Gin, a 31-year-old 
engineer and business owner, and Frank Bostrom, an architect. 
</P>
<P>
 In District 5, the northernmost section of Redondo, City Councilwoman Marilyn 
White seeks a second term. She will face Kim Marie Lewis, a 34-year-old 
engineer, and Barry J. Brennan, a 27-year-old businessman. 
</P>
<P>
 Dec. 9 was the deadline for filing candidacy papers. JAMES BENNING 
