<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES COUNTY; 
SHERIFF WELCOMES REPORT OF DROP IN OFFICER SHOOTINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles County Sheriff Sherman Block says he welcomes a report that 
officer-involved shootings have declined in his department, saying deputies are 
"approaching suspects a little more cautiously than in the past." 
</P>
<P>
 "We arrest a lot of people with guns, we confiscate a lot of guns, and a lot 
of these could have resulted in shootings," Block said."But because of training 
and skills, our deputies are able to resolve them with less violence than 
otherwise would have occurred." 
</P>
<P>
 Referring to a three-year reform effort, Block said: "We are proceeding, I 
think, very aggressively and very objectively in instituting whatever 
appropriate changes are merited in our operations." 
</P>
