<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: AGOURA HILLS; MANN THEATRES TO BE PART OF NEW PROJECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MANNING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The developer of a proposed Agoura Hills commercial center has signed a 
30-year lease with Mann Theatres for the cinema chain to build and operate an 
eight-screen theater complex, according to the developer and city officials. 
</P>
<P>
 If approved by the city Planning Commission, the theater would be part of 
Creekside Terrace, a large commercial center with more than 150,000 square feet 
of shops, restaurants and offices at Agoura and Kanan roads. 
</P>
<P>
 The long-term lease greatly enhances the chances of success for the entire 
project because acquisition of a reputable anchor tenant will encourage other 
businesses to locate there, say representatives of the developer, Whizin 
Enterprises. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the lease, Mann Theatres will pay to build and operate the theater and 
pay rent to the developer, which will maintain ownership of the property. 
</P>
<P>
 Agoura Hills Community Development Director David Anderson said the city is 
conducting an environmental review of the project. The Planning Commission may 
vote on the project as early as the spring. 
</P>
<P>
 Mann Theatres, which already operates an eight-screen cineplex on Agoura Road, 
believes that the area needs another theater because parking at the existing 
theater is a problem, Anderson said. A walkway will eventually be built between 
the two facilities as part of a plan to develop the entire area into an 
entertainment corridor next to the freeway, he said. FRANK MANNING 
</P>
</TEXT>
