</P>
<P>
 Several smaller public programs--agencies that do everything from giving 
Christmas gifts to the poor to killing mosquitoes--have money tied up in Orange 
County's bankrupt investment pool. The future of some of the programs is in 
jeopardy. Here is a sampling of the smaller investors: Fund: Amount in pool 
Victim/Witness Assistance: $723,822 Emergency Mosquito Abatement: $584,313 
