<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRAINS, TREES, CANDY CANES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Train sets and Christmas trees seem to go together like Santas and candy 
canes. But with 2,000 feet of train tracks, you know we're talking holiday 
celebration on a grand scale. 
</P>
<P>
 Old Pasadena is getting into the Christmas spirit with a Winter Wonderland 
that features train rides for $1, a 25-foot snowman (the inflatable type) and a 
15-foot Christmas tree. 
</P>
<P>
 A 25-foot-by-45-foot train village, with replicas of Old World European towns 
professionally lit with theatrical lights, is the centerpiece of the 
wonderland, along with nine collectors' edition train sets.  
</P>
<P>
 The festivities take place at One Colorado, a courtyard tucked behind brick 
facades in the middle of Old Town, near Fair Oaks Avenue.  
</P>
<P>
 Hours for the event are 10 a.m. to 9 p.m. Friday through Dec. 30. Santa will 
be on hand Saturday, Sunday and Dec. 23 from noon to 5 p.m. Information: (818) 
564-1066. LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
