<LENGTH>
<P>
97 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHECKPOINTS TO MONITOR DRINKING, SEAT BELT USE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Beginning in January, sheriff's deputies in La Puente will begin conducting 
monthly checkpoints for drunk driving and use of safety belts. 
</P>
<P>
 The city, which contracts with the county for deputies' services, was recently 
awarded a $91,000 grant from the California Office of Traffic Safety to begin 
the program.  
</P>
<P>
 A recent survey revealed that less than half the children younger than 4 in La 
Puente were in child-safety seats, as the law requires, when riding in a 
vehicle.  
</P>
<P>
 The first sobriety checkpoint will be on Jan. 6. The first seat-belt 
checkpoint will be on Jan. 21. 
</P>
