<TEXT>
<P>
 Correction: Oops. Nissan North America Inc. does have a car priced less than 
$14,000.In a listing here several weeks ago of car importers that will be 
offering one or more 1996 models under $10,000, Nissan's base four-door Altima 
XE, at $14,799, was shown as the company's least-expensive '96 model. Omitted 
was the entire 1996 Sentra line, which will not be available until January, 
according to the company's Torrance headquarters. None of the 1995 Sentras are 
priced below $10,000, but one comes close at $10,439. 
</P>
